Argentine Stocks: Aluar Aluminio, Pampa Energia Rise; YPF Falls

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-11T20:14:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/argentine-stocks-aluar-aluminio-pampa-energia-rise-ypf-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 1.1 percent to 3,384.57  Aluar Aluminio Argentino SAIC (ALUA)   gained 1.9 percent
to 5.28 pesos, its biggest increase in six weeks.  Argentina ’s
largest aluminum producer will be allowed to import goods for
the upgrade of one of its production facilities free from tariff
payments, according to an e-mailed statement from the local
Industry Ministry.  Pampa Energia SA (PAMP)   rose 1.2 percent to 2.58 pesos,
the steepest increase in more than a week and its third
consecutive day of gains. Argentina’s biggest power company
reached an agreement with Petrobras Energia SA, the local unit
of  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company Petroleo Brasileiro SA,
to end a legal dispute in a New York court over the defaulted
debt of Compania de Inversiones SA, or Ciesa.  YPF SA (YPFD)   fell 3.5 percent to 192.2 pesos, the
steepest decline in a week. Argentina’s largest company by
market value ceded some of the 5.7 percent gain it posted
yesterday after announcing it discovered the equivalent of about
150 million barrels of shale oil, the country’s largest
discovery in two decades.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
